description: Pro-democracy protesters have occupied parts of Hong Kong since September.
title: Maps of the Protest Sites in Hong Kong
title_page: Maps of the Protest Sites in Hong Kong - The New York Times
maintext:
Hong Kong MONG KOK
Mong Kok: Argyle Street and Nathan Road
In late November, hundreds of police officers seized control of Argyle Street and cleared encampments in a two-day confrontation with protesters. The police attempted to clear the site on Oct. 17 but were met with thousands of protesters who forced the officers to withdraw. Earlier in October, groups of criminal gangs attacked protesters in a failed effort to scatter them. No encampments remain, but some protesters still gather here.
